JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Police Commissioner Elias Mawela has confirmed that a fifth person passed away in hospital following Wednesday’s mob violence in Zandspruit. Three people have also since been arrested. Nine young men were taken to a local field on Wednesday morning where they were beaten up by a group of community members before being necklaced. READ: Zandspruit mob justice: Residents say they're tired of being terrorised They were accused of being behind a spate of crimes in the informal settlement. Mawela on Thursday said the three suspects in custody were part of the group that orchestrated the mob violence. “Three people were arrested, and they are from the vigilante group, which claims to be representing the community.” He also said the community of Zandspruit ha well-structured and coordinated community patrollers set up to deal with issues of crime in the area. WATCH: Zandspruit mob justice: What led to 4 deaths and multiple injuries?  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.